<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/duncan-capps> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Major General Duncan Capps CBE is a former senior British Army officer. Most recently he has been Director for the Home Office Maritime and Small Boats Command, leading the government’s operational response to small boat crossings, maritime security and overseeing the  Joint Maritime Security Centre . He served as Commandant of the Royal Military Academy, Sandhurst from March 2020 to August 2022, having previously held senior operational command and logistics roles in the British Army, including leadership of deployed operations in Cyprus, Northern Ireland, Bosnia, the Middle East, Africa and Afghanistan."@en .
